> If you're a grazer who'd rather eat apps than entrées (no judgments here!), this is a fantastic dinner plan for you. We're excited to present lots of delicious nibbles you can eat with your fingers (or with a pita or a cuke dipper—you get the idea!). You've got hummus, a refreshing shredded cucumber and dill yogurt sauce, toasted pita wedges, fresh cucumber and carrot dippers, and our crowning glory: succulent pan-seared shrimp simmered in a garlicky herbed tomato sauce. Go ahead, take a dip, the mezze's fine!

== Tzatziki ==

Wash and dry produce.

Trim and grate half the @cucumber{1} on the largest holes of a #box grater{}; slice remaining cucumber into sticks (like fries; ours were about 4 inches long and ½ inch thick). Place grated cucumber in the center of a clean #kitchen towel{} (or a couple layers of #paper towels{}) and toss with a big pinch of @salt{}; set aside.

Pick @dill{¼%ounce} fronds from stems; finely chop fronds. Quarter @lemon{1}. Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{6%ounce} into sticks (like fries; ours were about 3 inches long and ½ inch thick).

Gather towel with grated cucumber into a tight bundle and wring over the sink to remove excess moisture.

In a #small bowl{} (medium bowl for 4 servings), combine grated cucumber with @yogurt{4%tablespoon}, @crème fraîche{4%tablespoon}, half the dill, half the @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon}, and a squeeze of lemon juice. Season with salt and @pepper{}.

== Shrimp ==

Rinse @shrimp{10%ounce} under cold water, then pat dry with paper towels.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a large #pan{} over medium-high heat. Add shrimp, @dried oregano{1%teaspoon}, remaining garlic powder, salt, and pepper. Cook, stirring, until shrimp are opaque and mostly cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Stir in @veggie stock concentrate{1} and half the @crushed tomatoes{13.76%ounce} (all for 4 servings). Cook, stirring, until tomatoes are jammy and shrimp are cooked through, ~{2-4%minutes} more. Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

> Shrimp are fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.

== To Serve ==

While shrimp cooks, toast @pita bread{2}; cut each pita into six triangles.

Transfer shrimp to a #medium bowl{}; sprinkle with as much remaining dill as you like. Place @hummus{½%cup} in a second small bowl.

Arrange bowls of shrimp, hummus, and tzatziki on a large #board{} or #platter{}. Serve family style with pita wedges, cucumber spears, carrot sticks, and remaining lemon wedges alongside.